Type casting in java - Type casting refers to changing the entity of one data type into another.

Syntax - Type variable1 =(type)_variable2;

Example: int x=60;
         byte n=(byte) x;
         double x=(int) y;

Java Type Casting :  Type casting means converting one data type into another. For example, turning an int into a double.

In Java, there are two main types of casting:

Widening Casting (automatic) - converting a smaller type to a larger type size
byte -> short -> char -> int -> long -> float -> double

Narrowing Casting (manual) - converting a larger type to a smaller type size
double -> float -> long -> int -> char -> short -> byte
